In 2015, the average rate on ruble bank loans, which are the company's main loans, increased to 12.55% (from 11.51% in 2014). Interest payments doubled from RUB 4 billion to RUB 8 billion over the same period. In the structure of the balance sheet, the capital indicator went negative, which is one of the signals of a possible pre-bankruptcy state of the enterprise.[44]
According to the results of the first quarter of 2016, the company's net loss amounted to 8.589 billion rubles against 178 million rubles, that is, 47 times more than in the same period of 2015.